27 proposed. Finally, section 2 provides that regardless of whether a proposed ordinance is
28 referred to a committee, at a regular or special meeting of the City Council, the title of the
29 proposed ordinance must be read and the City Council must vote to adopt, revise or postpone
30 consideration of the proposed ordinance.
31 The existing Charter of the City of Henderson: (1) authorizes the City Council to sell
32 unimproved real property owned by the City on a time payment basis; and (2) requires that
33 when the City Council disposes of real property to certain entities, the consideration paid must
34 equal the cost of the acquisition to the City. (Henderson City Charter § 2.320) Section 3 of
35 this bill authorizes the City Council to instead sell any real property owned by the City on a
36 time payment basis. Section 3 also : (1) removes the requirement that the consideration paid
37 for the disposal of real property to certain entities must equal the cost of the acquisition to the
38 City [.] ; and (2) provides that such disposals of real property are subject to certain
39 provisions of the Nevada Revised Statutes governing municipal property to the extent
40 such provisions are applicable.
